#: app_ai/views.py:1801 app_ai/views.py:2113 app_ai/views.py:2228
#: app_ai/views.py:2236 app_ai/views.py:2242
msgid ""
"Compliance Management Dashboard - Overview of compliance frameworks, "
"controls, and their status"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1802 app_ai/views.py:2237 app_ai/views.py:2243
msgid ""
"This is the main compliance management dashboard where you can view "
"compliance frameworks (like ISO 27001, PCI DSS, GDPR), manage controls, "
"track compliance status, monitor implementation progress, and access "
"compliance-related reports and analytics."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1804
msgid ""
"Local Compliance Management - Managing local regulatory compliance "
"requirements and controls"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1805
msgid ""
"This page is for managing local compliance requirements, regulatory "
"controls, evidence, and assignments for specific countries or regions."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1807
msgid ""
"Compliance Frameworks Management - Creating and managing compliance "
"frameworks (ISO 27001, PCI DSS, GDPR, etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1808
msgid ""
"This section allows you to create, edit, and manage compliance frameworks, "
"their categories, and controls."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1810
msgid ""
"Compliance Controls - Managing individual compliance controls, evidence, and "
"assignments"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1811
msgid ""
"This page is for managing specific compliance controls, adding evidence, "
"assigning responsible users, and tracking implementation status."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1813
msgid "Compliance Evidence - Managing evidence for compliance controls"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1814
msgid ""
"This page allows you to upload, review, approve, or reject evidence "
"documents for compliance controls."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1816
msgid "Compliance Management page"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1817
msgid "This is a compliance management page in the SecBoard platform."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1823
msgid ""
"Risk Assessment - Evaluating and analyzing security risks for information "
"assets"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1824
msgid ""
"This page allows you to assess risks associated with information assets, "
"vulnerabilities, and threats."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1826
msgid "Risk Treatment - Managing risk mitigation and treatment plans"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1827
msgid ""
"This page is for creating and managing risk treatment plans, assigning "
"responsibilities, and tracking treatment status."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1829 app_ai/views.py:2117
msgid "Risk Assessment and Management page"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1830 app_ai/views.py:2118
msgid ""
"This is a risk management page where you can assess and manage information "
"security risks."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1838
msgid "Incident Register - List of security incidents and their status"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1839
msgid ""
"This page displays the incident register with all security incidents. You "
"can view, search, filter incidents by status, severity, date, and other "
"criteria. Export incidents to Excel and manage incident lifecycle."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1841
msgid "Add Incident - Reporting a new security incident"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1842
msgid ""
"This page allows you to report a new security incident. You can provide "
"incident details, classification, severity, affected systems, initial "
"response actions, and attach relevant files or evidence."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1844
msgid ""
"Incident Detail - Viewing detailed information about a specific security "
"incident"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1845
msgid ""
"This page displays detailed information about a specific security incident "
"including incident timeline, affected systems, response actions, evidence, "
"attachments, and incident status updates."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1847
msgid "Edit Incident - Updating incident information and status"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1848
msgid ""
"This page allows you to edit an existing security incident. You can update "
"incident details, change status, add response actions, update affected "
"systems, and modify incident classification."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1850
msgid "Export Incidents - Exporting incident data to Excel"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1851
msgid ""
"This page allows you to export security incidents data to Excel format for "
"reporting, analysis, and documentation purposes."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1853 app_ai/views.py:2121
msgid ""
"Incident Management - Managing security incidents, response activities, and "
"post-incident reviews"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1854 app_ai/views.py:2122
msgid ""
"This page is for reporting, tracking, and managing security incidents, "
"including incident response activities, documentation, evidence collection, "
"and post-incident reviews."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1862
msgid "Information Assets - List of information assets and their details"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1863
msgid ""
"This page displays the list of all information assets in the system. You can "
"view, search, filter, and manage information assets, see their "
"classification, criticality levels, owners, and administrators."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1865
msgid "Add Information Asset - Creating a new information asset"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1866
msgid ""
"This page allows you to create a new information asset. You can specify "
"asset details, classification, criticality level, assign owners and "
"administrators, and configure asset protection requirements."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1868
msgid "Edit Information Asset - Editing asset details and configuration"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1869
msgid ""
"This page allows you to edit an existing information asset. You can modify "
"asset properties, classification, criticality, update owners and "
"administrators, and change protection requirements."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1871
msgid ""
"Asset Types Management - Managing types and categories of information assets"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1872
msgid ""
"This page allows you to manage asset types and categories. You can create, "
"edit, and organize different types of information assets used in the "
"classification system."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1874
msgid "Asset Groups Management - Organizing assets into groups and categories"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1875
msgid ""
"This page is for managing asset groups. You can organize information assets "
"into groups and categories for better management and organization."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1877
msgid "Asset Owners Management - Assigning and managing asset owners"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1878
msgid ""
"This page allows you to manage asset owners. You can assign owners to "
"information assets, view ownership relationships, and manage "
"responsibilities."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1880
msgid ""
"Asset Administrators Management - Assigning and managing asset administrators"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1881
msgid ""
"This page is for managing asset administrators. You can assign "
"administrators to information assets, configure administrative "
"responsibilities, and manage administrative access."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1883
msgid "Export Assets - Exporting asset data to Excel"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1884
msgid ""
"This page allows you to export information assets data to Excel format for "
"reporting and analysis purposes."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1886 app_ai/views.py:2125
msgid ""
"Asset Management - Managing information assets, their classification, and "
"protection requirements"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1887
msgid ""
"This page allows you to manage information assets, classify them by "
"criticality, assign owners and administrators, and track their protection "
"status."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1892
msgid ""
"Vulnerability Management - Identifying, assessing, and managing security "
"vulnerabilities"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1893
msgid ""
"This page is for managing security vulnerabilities, their assessment, "
"remediation, and tracking."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1901
msgid "Access Records - Managing access records for information systems"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1902
msgid ""
"This page allows you to view, create, edit, and manage access records for "
"information systems. You can assign access rights, roles, and permissions to "
"users and groups for different systems and objects."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1904
msgid ""
"Access Matrix - Viewing and managing access matrix for information systems"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1905
msgid ""
"This page displays the access matrix showing relationships between roles, "
"objects, and access rights. You can view and manage access mappings for "
"information systems."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1907
msgid "Access Request - Requesting access to information systems"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1908
msgid ""
"This page allows users to submit access requests for information systems. "
"You can request access to specific systems, objects, roles, and access "
"rights."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1910
msgid "Manage Access Requests - Reviewing and approving access requests"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1911
msgid ""
"This page is for administrators to review, approve, or reject access "
"requests. You can manage the approval workflow, assign approvers, and track "
"request status."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1913
msgid "Access Configuration - Configuring access rights, roles, and functions"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1914
msgid ""
"This page allows you to configure access rights, roles, functions, and "
"objects for information systems. You can define access levels and "
"permissions."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1916
msgid "Functions Management - Managing functions for information systems"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1917
msgid ""
"This page is for managing functions (capabilities) available in information "
"systems. You can create, edit, and organize functions used in access "
"configurations."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1919
msgid "Objects Management - Managing access objects for information systems"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1920
msgid ""
"This page allows you to manage access objects (resources, modules, "
"components) within information systems. You can create hierarchical object "
"structures and assign access rights."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1922
msgid "Roles Management - Managing roles for access control"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1923
msgid ""
"This page is for managing roles used in access control. You can define "
"roles, assign functions and access rights to them."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1925
msgid "API Access Management - Managing API access and synchronization"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1926
msgid ""
"This page allows you to manage API access requests, configure API "
"credentials, synchronize users, and monitor API access status."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1928
msgid "Available Access - Viewing available access options"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1929
msgid ""
"This page shows available access options that users can request. You can "
"browse systems, objects, roles, and access rights available for request."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1931
msgid "Access Notifications - Configuring access-related email notifications"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1932
msgid ""
"This page allows you to configure email notifications for access requests, "
"approvals, and other access-related events."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1934 app_ai/views.py:2133
msgid "Access Management - Managing access to information systems"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1935 app_ai/views.py:2134
msgid ""
"This is an access management page where you can manage access to information "
"systems, configure access rights, roles, and permissions."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1943
msgid ""
"GDPR Compliance Dashboard - Overview of GDPR compliance status and activities"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1944
msgid ""
"This is the GDPR compliance dashboard providing an overview of data "
"protection compliance, data subjects, consents, data breach incidents, and "
"compliance metrics."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1946
msgid "Data Subjects Management - Managing personal data subjects"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1947
msgid ""
"This page allows you to manage data subjects (individuals whose personal "
"data is processed). You can add, edit, view, export, and anonymize personal "
"data for GDPR compliance."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1949
msgid "Consent Records - Managing consent records for data processing"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1950
msgid ""
"This page is for managing consent records. You can track consent given by "
"data subjects for data processing activities, view consent history, and "
"manage consent withdrawals."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1952
msgid "Data Subject Requests (DSR) - Managing GDPR data subject requests"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1953
msgid ""
"This page allows you to manage Data Subject Requests (DSR) such as access "
"requests, rectification, erasure, and data portability. You can create, "
"process, and track DSR compliance."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1955
msgid "Data Breach Incidents - Managing and reporting data breach incidents"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1956
msgid ""
"This page is for managing data breach incidents. You can report breaches, "
"track incident details, assess risk, and generate breach reports for "
"regulatory compliance."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1958
msgid ""
"Data Processing Activities - Managing data processing activities register"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1959
msgid ""
"This page allows you to manage the register of data processing activities "
"(Article 30 GDPR). You can document how personal data is processed, for what "
"purposes, and by whom."
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1961
msgid "Data Retention Policies - Managing data retention and deletion policies"
msgstr ""

#: app_ai/views.py:1962
msgid ""
"This page is for managing data retention policies. You can define how long "
