#: app_conf/views.py:2830
msgid "How does maturity assessment work?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2831
msgid ""
"Maturity assessment uses 0-5 scale: 0 (Not Implemented), 1 (Initial), 2 "
"(Developing), 3 (Defined), 4 (Managed), 5 (Optimized). Each control is "
"evaluated, evidence is collected, and maturity score is assigned. Historical "
"assessments track improvement over time."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2834
msgid "Can I map controls across frameworks?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2835
msgid ""
"Yes, module supports cross-framework control mapping. Many controls are "
"common across frameworks (e.g., access control, encryption, monitoring). "
"Mapping enables single implementation to satisfy multiple framework "
"requirements, reducing duplication and effort."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2839
msgid ""
"Gap analysis compares current maturity against target maturity for each "
"control. Module identifies controls below target, calculates gap size, "
"prioritizes based on risk and impact, and generates remediation "
"recommendations. Track remediation progress and re-assess to close gaps."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2842
msgid "Can I customize frameworks?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2843
msgid ""
"Yes, you can create custom frameworks, modify existing frameworks, add "
"custom controls, define custom maturity scales, and tailor assessment "
"questions. Module is flexible to support organization-specific compliance "
"requirements and internal standards."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2846
msgid "How do I prepare for audits?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2847
msgid ""
"Module generates audit-ready documentation including compliance status "
"reports, control implementation evidence, maturity scores, gap analysis, "
"remediation plans, and historical assessment records. Export reports in PDF "
"or Excel format for auditors and regulators."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2861
msgid "Module not found"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2889
msgid "General Questions"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2894
msgid "What is SecBoard?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2895
msgid ""
"SecBoard is a comprehensive information security management platform that "
"integrates multiple security modules including risk assessment, incident "
"management, compliance tracking, security awareness training, and more. It "
"provides organizations with a unified solution for managing their "
"cybersecurity posture."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2898
msgid "Is SecBoard customizable?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2899
msgid ""
"Yes, SecBoard is highly flexible and allows quick customization and "
"adaptation to meet specific client requirements and business needs."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2902
msgid "What technologies does SecBoard use?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2903
msgid ""
"SecBoard is built on Django (Python web framework), Bootstrap 5 for UI, "
"PostgreSQL/SQLite for database, Celery for async tasks, Redis for caching, "
"and integrates with various security tools like Wazuh and GoPhish."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2906
msgid "Who can use SecBoard?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2907
msgid ""
"SecBoard is designed for security professionals, compliance officers, risk "
"managers, IT administrators, and organizations of any size looking to "
"implement comprehensive information security management."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2912
msgid "Security & Access"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2917
msgid "How secure is SecBoard?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2918
msgid ""
"SecBoard implements multiple security layers including multi-factor "
"authentication (MFA), role-based access control (RBAC), session management, "
"encrypted data storage, CSRF protection, XSS prevention, and comprehensive "
"audit logging. All security best practices are followed."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2921
msgid "Does SecBoard support multi-factor authentication?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2922
msgid ""
"Yes, SecBoard supports multi-factor authentication to enhance account "
"security and prevent unauthorized access."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2925
msgid "How does role-based access control work?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2926
msgid ""
"SecBoard uses Django's permission system with custom groups and permissions. "
"Administrators can create roles, assign specific permissions to each role, "
"and control what users can see and do based on their role assignments."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2929
msgid "Can I control who has access to specific modules?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2930
msgid ""
"Yes, access to each module and feature can be controlled through the "
"permission system. You can grant or revoke access at a granular level."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2935
msgid "Features & Modules"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2940
msgid "What modules are included in SecBoard?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2941
msgid ""
"SecBoard includes 11 main modules: Security Awareness Training, User "
"Cabinet, Document Management, Risk Assessment, Asset Management, Key/"
"Certificate Management, Incident Management, Standards & Compliance, Access "
"Management, SOC (Security Operations Center), and Phishing Simulation "
"(GoPhish integration)."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2944
msgid "Can I use only specific modules?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2945
msgid ""
"Yes, SecBoard is modular. You can enable or disable specific modules based "
"on your organization's needs."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2948
msgid "Does SecBoard integrate with existing security tools?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2949
msgid ""
"Yes, SecBoard can integrate with various security tools. Currently, it "
"supports integration with Wazuh (SIEM), GoPhish (phishing simulation), and "
"provides REST APIs for custom integrations."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2952
msgid "What compliance standards does SecBoard support?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2953
msgid ""
"SecBoard supports multiple compliance frameworks including ISO 27001, ISO "
"27002, NIST Cybersecurity Framework, PCI DSS, and GDPR. The Standards & "
"Compliance module includes templates and controls for these frameworks."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2963
msgid "How does risk assessment work in SecBoard?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2964
msgid ""
"SecBoard provides a comprehensive risk assessment module that allows you to "
"identify assets, threats, and vulnerabilities, calculate risk levels using "
"customizable matrices, implement risk treatment plans, and track risk over "
"time with detailed reporting."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2967
msgid "Can I customize risk matrices?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2968
msgid ""
"Yes, you can fully customize risk assessment methodologies, impact scales, "
"likelihood scales, and risk matrices to match your organization's risk "
"management framework."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2971
msgid "Does SecBoard support threat modeling?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2972
msgid ""
"Yes, the Risk Assessment module includes threat modeling capabilities where "
"you can identify potential threats to your assets and assess their impact."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2977
msgid "Training & Awareness"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2982
msgid "What training features are available?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2983
msgid ""
"SecBoard includes a complete Learning Management System (LMS) with "
"interactive courses, quizzes, certification tracking, progress monitoring, "
"and customizable training materials. You can create custom courses or use "
"pre-built security awareness content."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2986
msgid "Can I create custom training courses?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2987
msgid ""
"Yes, the Training module allows you to create custom courses with text, "
"images, videos, and interactive quizzes. You can organize content into "
"modules and track learner progress."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2990
msgid "Does SecBoard support phishing simulation?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:2991
msgid ""
"Yes, through GoPhish integration, you can run phishing simulation campaigns, "
"create custom email templates and landing pages, and track user responses to "
"improve security awareness."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3001
msgid "How does incident management work?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3002
msgid ""
"The Incident Management module provides a complete workflow for handling "
"security incidents including incident registration, classification, "
"investigation tracking, escalation procedures, remediation actions, and post-"
"incident reporting."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3005
msgid "Can I customize incident workflows?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3006
msgid ""
"Yes, you can customize incident types, severity levels, status workflows, "
"escalation rules, and notification procedures to match your incident "
"response plan."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3009
msgid "Does SecBoard track incident metrics?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3010
msgid ""
"Yes, the system provides comprehensive incident analytics including response "
"times, resolution rates, incident trends, and compliance metrics."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3015
msgid "Installation & Setup"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3020
msgid "What are the system requirements?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3021
msgid ""
"SecBoard requires Python 3.8+, Django 5.0+, a database (PostgreSQL "
"recommended, SQLite for development), Redis for caching and Celery tasks, "
"and a modern web browser. Minimum 2GB RAM and 10GB disk space recommended."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3024
msgid "How do I install SecBoard?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3025
msgid ""
"Installation involves cloning the repository, installing Python "
"dependencies, configuring the database, running migrations, creating a "
"superuser, and starting the Django development server. Detailed installation "
"instructions are provided in the documentation."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3028
msgid "Can SecBoard be deployed in production?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3029
msgid ""
"Yes, SecBoard can be deployed in production using WSGI servers like Gunicorn "
"or uWSGI with Nginx as a reverse proxy. It includes production-ready "
"security settings and can be containerized with Docker."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3032
msgid "Is there a demo available?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3033
msgid ""
"Yes, you can access a live demo at demo.secboard.online to explore the "
"platform's features before installation."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3038
msgid "Support & Community"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3043
msgid "Where can I get help?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3044
msgid ""
"You can get help through the project documentation, GitHub issues, community "
"forums, or by contacting the SecBoard team directly via email or Telegram."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3047
msgid "How can I contribute to SecBoard?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3048
msgid ""
"Contributions are welcome! You can contribute by submitting bug reports, "
"feature requests, pull requests, documentation improvements, or "
"translations. Check the GitHub repository for contribution guidelines."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3051
msgid "Is commercial support available?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3052
msgid ""
"Yes, commercial support, customization services, and consulting are "
"available. Contact the SecBoard team for more information."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3055
msgid "What languages does SecBoard support?"
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3056
msgid ""
"SecBoard currently supports English, Ukrainian, and Russian. The platform is "
"built with internationalization support, making it easy to add new languages."
msgstr ""

#: app_conf/views.py:3065
msgid ""
"Find answers to frequently asked questions about SecBoard - the "
"comprehensive information security management platform. Learn about "
"features, installation, security, and more."
msgstr ""

